.TH MDNS\-LOOKUP 1 "2026-04-15" "truenas-pydiscovery" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mdns\-lookup \- look up a named mDNS service instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mdns\-lookup
.RB [ \-t
.IR TIMEOUT ]
.RB [ \-i
.IR ADDR ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.I NAME SERVICE_TYPE
.RI [ DOMAIN ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mdns\-lookup
resolves a named service instance to its contact information:
hostname, port, and TXT records.
Equivalent to
.BR "dns\-sd \-L" .
.PP
No daemon is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I NAME
Service instance name (e.g.\ \fBTN26NEW\fP).
.TP
.I SERVICE_TYPE
Service type (e.g.\ \fB_http._tcp\fP).
.TP
.I DOMAIN
Domain.
Default: \fBlocal\fP.
.TP
.BI \-t " TIMEOUT" "\fR,\fP \-\-timeout " TIMEOUT
Query timeout in seconds.
Default: 3.0.
.TP
.BI \-i " ADDR" "\fR,\fP \-\-interface " ADDR
Interface IPv4 address to send queries from.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSON.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
mdns\-lookup TN26NEW _http._tcp
mdns\-lookup "My NAS" _smb._tcp local \-\-json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mdns\-browse (1),
.BR mdns\-resolve (1),
.BR truenas\-mdnsd (8)
